{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idaba6c49b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12647"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"12647"},"text":"§ 12647.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Commissioned officers: retention in active status while assigned to Selective Service System or serving as United States property and fiscal officers","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding chapters 843, 1407, and 1409 of this title, a reserve commissioned officer, other than a commissioned warrant officer, who is assigned to the Selective Service System or who is a property and fiscal officer appointed, designated, or detailed under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t32/s708"},"text":"section 708 of title 32","children":[],"tail":", may be retained in an active status in that assignment or position until he becomes 62 years of age."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idaba6c49c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/861/s1/22/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–861, § 1(22)(B)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-09-02"},"text":"Sept. 2, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/1445"},"text":"72 Stat. 1445","children":[],"tail":", § 1007; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/559/s1/3/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–559, § 1(3)(B)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1960-06-30"},"text":"June 30, 1960","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/74/265"},"text":"74 Stat. 265","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 12647 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/dA/tXVI"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, div. A, title XVI","children":[],"tail":", §§ 1662(h)(2), 1675(d)(4), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994